  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Asked several times by Sen. Herb Kohl, DD-Wis.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   , about women's right to end their pregnancies, Thomas said, "Whether or not I have a view is irrelevant."; President Bush, asked at a news conference whether Thomas' claim not to have an opinion on abortion is credible, answered, "That's a question for the Senate to decide."; "He's handling himself very well," the president said.
  </a>
